  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.12005" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>April 25/84</dateline>
        <opener> My dear Professor:</opener>
        <p> Since receiving yr letter I have been thinking over your proposal to have the Berendt MS. on <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.378">
Nicaraguan</ref> words published in <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.97">Vienna</placeName>. It is a folio book, of 203 leaves, containing about 2000 words with their explanations, cleanly written, with a brief introduction. The full title is "Palabras y Modismos de la Lengua Castellana segun se habla en Nicaragua, colectados y coordinados por C. H. Berendt, M.D., 1874."<note
            n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Das Manuskript ist als <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.8811">Berendt (1874)</ref>
            </bibl> im Katalog der Bibliothek Brintons verzeichnet (<bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.3033">Weeks 2003: 72</ref>
            </bibl>). Es scheint nicht zu einer Publikation in Wien gekommen zu sein. Vgl. auch hier <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.letter.12007">Brief 6-01380</ref>.</note>
        </p>
        <p>If you can secure the following conditions from the Society, I will send the MS. to you for publication. </p>
        <p>1. That it will appear under the name of Dr. <persName>

Berendt</persName>. </p>
        <p>2. That the publication will be commenced in not less than one year from the date of receipt of the MS. </p>
        <p> 3. That ten copies of the work <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> when printed will be sent me free of charge. </p>
        <p> 4. That the usual honorarium will be paid. </p>
        <p> This last I propose that you and I divide. It don't amount to much, to be sure, but whatever it is, that would be the most equitable adjustment, as I supply the material and you see it through the press. </p>
        <p>If you wish further information on the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.768">Florida Spanish dialects</ref>, I am told that the best authority is the Hon. G. R. Fairbanks,<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <persName>

George Rainsford Fairbanks</persName> (1820-1906) war ein nordamerikanische Anwalt, Gründer und Präsident der 
<hi
              rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
Florida Historical Society</hi>
, ebenso wie Gründer der 
<hi
              rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
University of the South at Sewanee</hi>
 (cf.<bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.8794"> DuBose 1906</ref>
            </bibl>, <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.8812">Henneman 1906</ref>
            </bibl>). Briefe an Schuchardt liegen nicht vor.</note> Fernandina, Florida. </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Very truly yrs</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1203"> D. G. Brinton</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
